    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-07-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-07-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="478"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                <head>No. 478.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Morgan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-07-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 13, 1880</date>. (Received July
                        29.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 51.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your Department dispatch No. 28 was received this
                    morning.</p>
                <p>In my note of the 26th June to the minister for foreign relations, I limited
                    myself to warning the Mexican Government that the United States would not be
                    responsible for any depredations which the Indians who had fled from the pursuit
                    of General Hatch might commit upon Mexicans.</p>
                <p>I now inclose copy of note addressed by me to the minister for foreign relations,
                    from which you will see that I have, in obedience to your instructions, notified
                    the Mexican Government that they will be held accountable for any damage which
                    these Indians may do to Americans, should they cross into our territory.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>P. H. MORGAN.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 51.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Morgan</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Ruelas</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-07-13">
                                <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 13, 1880</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my notes of the 21st and 26th of
                        June last, I am now instructed by my government to say to your excellency
                        that the accordance of asylum to the enemies of the United States flying
                        over the border when under pursuit involves in its apprehension an urgent
                        obligation on the part of the Mexican Government to disarm the Indians
                        referred to in my notes of the above dates, and a responsibility on the part
                        of the Mexican Government for any future inroads upon United States
                        territory they may make.</p>
                    <p>I improve this opportunity to renew to your excellency the assurances of my
                        very distinguished consideration.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>P. H. MORGAN.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
